      <title>Deadly Wisconsin school shooting. And, a pig kidney transplant surgery provides hope</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/12/17/g-s1-38574/up-first-newsletter-deadly-school-shooting-madison-wisconsin-donald-trump-press-conference-pig-kidney-transplant</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2024/12/17/g-s1-38574/up-first-newsletter-deadly-school-shooting-madison-wisconsin-donald-trump-press-conference-pig-kidney-transplant</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2024/12/17/g-s1-38574/up-first-newsletter-deadly-school-shooting-madison-wisconsin-donald-trump-press-conference-pig-kidney-transplant</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 17 Dec 2024 13:02:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A grieving community gathered at a Madison, Wis., church last night after a 15-year-old girl opened fire at Abundant Life Christian School.&lt;/strong&gt; A teacher and a student were killed in the shooting. The suspect, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/16/g-s1-38488/madison-wisconsin-school-shooting-abundant-life-christian" target="_blank"&gt;identified as Natalie Rupnow&lt;/a&gt;, who also goes by Samantha, died of what's believed to be a self-inflicted gunshot wound. Six other people were injured. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/17/nx-s1-5231482/what-to-know-school-shooting-madison-wisconsin" target="_blank"&gt;Here's what else we know&lt;/a&gt; about the shooting.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-38539" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1e%2F0f%2Fe60a669a47a686c0cc0cb4b04c69%2Fgettyimages-2189784876.jpg" class="img" alt="Students from Abundant Life Christian School are escorted to a city bus to be reunited with their parents after a school shooting on Dec. 16, 2024 in Madison, Wis." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Students from Abundant Life Christian School are escorted to a city bus to be reunited with their parents after a school shooting on Dec. 16, 2024 in Madison, Wis.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Andy Manis/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Police confirmed that a second grader called 911 to report the school shooting&lt;/strong&gt;, Sarah Lehr of NPR network station Wisconsin Public Radio says. They believe the shooting happened inside a study hall. As of late yesterday, police say two students remain in critical condition. Mireille Jean-Charles, a mother of three boys who go to the school, told Lehr that though they are uninjured, she &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1219887504:1263672914" target="_blank"&gt;expects they'll have emotional trauma&lt;/a&gt; for a long time. Authorities say they are still trying to piece together a motive behind the shooting. They recovered a handgun at the scene and are working to trace its origins.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President-elect Donald Trump held his first press conference since the election at his Mar-a-Lago resort in Florida yesterday.&lt;/strong&gt; For over an hour, he discussed a range of topics, from concerns about his choice for health secretary, Robert F. Kennedy Jr., to his promise to bring prices down. NPR's Mara Liasson says Trump expressed that everything was pretty much perfect when he was in office before, and things will be great again with him returning to the White House. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Trump says everyone is trying to be his friend, and Liasson tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt; there are some factors behind this.&lt;/strong&gt; He is seen as a more legitimate president for his second term after winning the popular vote. There's also expected anticipation from the business community for a Republican president in office. People are &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1219887504:1263672914" target="_blank"&gt;approaching Trump differently and choosing their battles&lt;/a&gt;, believing his mind can be changed on certain ideas and policies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the first time, surgeons have implanted a new kind of engineered pig kidney into a living person. &lt;/strong&gt;The milestone surgery is part of the quest to use genetically modified farm animals to save patients with failing organs. Towana Looney, a 53-year-old grandmother, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2024/12/17/nx-s1-5203056/pig-kidney-transplant-gene-edited" target="_blank"&gt;received the surgery&lt;/a&gt; at the NYU Langone Health Hospital in New York City. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;NPR's Rob Stein got exclusive access to the operating room during the seven-hour procedure, which took place on Nov. 25. &lt;/strong&gt;The hope is that eventually, genetically modified pigs could provide an unlimited supply of kidneys, livers, hearts and other organs to help solve the organ shortage. Stein, who visited Looney two weeks after the surgery, says she is doing fine so far. Looney said &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1219887504:1263672914" target="_blank"&gt;she feels like she got a second chance at life&lt;/a&gt;. There are worries about pig organs spreading dangerous viruses to people, breeding and slaughtering pigs for their organs and experimenting on desperately ill patients.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Deep dive&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-38249" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2000;         --source-height: 1125;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+275/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F31%2Fb7%2F4f6ce28241a680b36aac54d35afa%2Fgettyimages-1162913033.jpg" class="img" alt="Stock photo of sweet shop pic and mix display of sugar coated red jelly sweet / gummy drops." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Stock photo of sweet shop pic and mix display of sugar coated red jelly sweet / gummy drops.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          mtreasure/Getty Images/iStockphoto                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Food and Drug Administration is considering banning Red No. 3, a petroleum-based food dye that has been used for more than 50 years&lt;/strong&gt; in thousands of products, from candy to soda. The petition to ban the colorant has been under review since 2022, but an &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2024/12/13/nx-s1-5228177/red-dye-3-fda-ban" target="_blank"&gt;FDA spokesperson tells NPR a decision could come "soon."&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🔴 &lt;strong&gt;The dye could cause cancer in animals in high doses&lt;/strong&gt;, but the agency determined it was safe in the amounts used in food.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🔴 &lt;strong&gt;California passed a law banning Red No. 3 last year. &lt;/strong&gt;Lawmakers in 10 other states have introduced legislation to ban the dye in foods.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🔴 &lt;strong&gt;California's Environmental Protection Agency reviewed research on synthetic dyes and found&lt;/strong&gt; evidence that when consumed in food, they can negatively impact children's behavior.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🔴 &lt;strong&gt;Red No. 3 has been banned or severely restricted in many countries&lt;/strong&gt;, including Australia, Japan and countries in the European Union.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-37979" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+182/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc1%2Fc5%2F5e6adedb41a48bc7ea08b8356408%2Frap-20241115-robopalooza-npr-0508.jpg 1800