      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;div id="resg-s1-38430" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 4000;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F25%2F9849d5014b2493ecfe0a5fd9b3b9%2Fgettyimages-1704939700.jpg" class="img" type="image/webp" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F25%2F9849d5014b2493ecfe0a5fd9b3b9%2Fgettyimages-1704939700.jpg" data-format="webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F25%2F9849d5014b2493ecfe0a5fd9b3b9%2Fgettyimages-1704939700.jpg" class="img" type="image/jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F25%2F9849d5014b2493ecfe0a5fd9b3b9%2Fgettyimages-1704939700.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F25%2F9849d5014b2493ecfe0a5fd9b3b9%2Fgettyimages-1704939700.jpg" class="img" alt="People stroll at Place des Vosges during a sunny afternoon in Paris on Oct. 3, 2023." data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F25%2F9849d5014b2493ecfe0a5fd9b3b9%2Fgettyimages-1704939700.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 People stroll at Place des Vosges during a sunny afternoon in Paris on Oct. 3, 2023.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Dimitar Dilkoff/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;December is going by swiftly. Before you know it we will hear the famous New Year's Eve countdown. With the end of the year comes reflection on all we have accomplished — and maybe some things we didn't. Our missteps can come with key lessons learned, and the &lt;em&gt;Up First &lt;/em&gt;newsletter team wants to hear from people who want to share theirs. We not only want to hear the biggest lessons you might have learned this year, but how you plan to implement them next year and going forward. Your guidance could help others.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you have experienced a key life lesson, share your story with us via the form below, and you could be featured in the &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt; newsletter on Dec. 29. You can also share a photo and upload your answers as a voice memo. &lt;strong&gt;Please submit responses by Dec. 20.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;See some of your responses — and get the news you need to start your day — by &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;u&gt;subscribing to our newsletter&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-38428-100" class="bucketwrap statichtml"&gt;             &lt;iframe src="https://npr.formstack.com/forms/biggest_lessons_learned" title="Formstack Form" width="100%" height="1200"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESG-S1-38428-100" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP STATICHTML" --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your submission will be governed by our general &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/about-npr/179876898/terms-of-use" target="_blank"&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/about-npr/179878450/privacy-policy" target="_blank"&gt;Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;. As the Privacy Policy says, we want you to be aware that there may be circumstances in which the exemptions provided under law for journalistic activities or freedom of expression may override privacy rights you might otherwise have.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
